\section{Oscillation Probability with Logarithmic Correction}
The neutrino oscillation probability receives a correction:
\begin{equation}
P_{\alpha\to\beta}(E) = \delta_{\alpha\beta} - 4 \sum_{i>j} \Re(U_{\alpha i}U_{\beta i}^*U_{\alpha j}^*U_{\beta j}) \sin^2\left( \frac{(\Delta m_{ij}^2 + \epsilon \log(E/E_0)) L}{4E} \right),
\end{equation}
where $\epsilon \sim 10^{-5}$ eV$^2$ represents the crystal-induced correction.  

