\section{Conclusion}
The Hamiltonian Crystal framework unifies neutrino masses and vacuum energy via a discrete Fock-space lattice. Gauge-invariant portal couplings generate Dirac-type neutrino masses, while spectral gaps produce a dynamic vacuum energy. The predicted logarithmic corrections to oscillation probabilities are experimentally falsifiable, offering a direct test of the framework.

